My family and I ordered a lot from the menu today and we loved it! The food was probably the most authentic I've had since moving.  The egg drop soup was average and the sizzling rice soup didn't have meat, but the tofu dry pot and eggplant was delicious! Highly recommend the bubble tea and chive dumplings.  The portion sizes are great and nothing was too anything (oily.salty, sugary, etc). If you're looking for a new, flavorful chinese spot to try- you got to try this place. Also, they gave us some free cakes and we were actually celebrating my birthday so that was really sweet.

I had to read through the reviews again to make sure I’d been to the same restaurant that people were complementing...this was one of the worst restaurant experiences I’ve ever had. The restaurant only had a few tables occupied when my party came in, no one greeted us, there wasn’t anyone on the floor or counter, it was ten minutes later that someone appeared with menus. We each ordered separately and our food arrived one by one, all at different times. The scallion pancakes were the last to arrive, burnt and inedible with the exception of two pieces where it was possible to eat around the burned edges. The braised eggplants was bland and stodgy, the sauce vaguely grainy. The dan dan noddles were tasty, if sweet. No one checked in with us to see how the food was. I had to get up to ask for water, because our waters hadn’t be refilled since we sat down. Instead of coming by the table to check if we needed anything, such as refill the rest of the waters on the table, the waiter disappeared. We asked for the check twice, the restaurant was empty except for us by now (it was only 10), and yet it took the waiter another 10 minutes to finally bring it to the table. The prices on our check didn’t match those advertised on the menu. When I confronted the waiter about it he gave me all sorts of excuses, including: 1) the price on the computer is the right price, 2) these are old menus, 3) we ordered something different, 4) the price on the menu is for a starter side not an entree, 5) he would have to call a manager and ask, it would be difficult, he insinuated. I was perplexed by now. He came back to our table only seconds later with the prices changed, it had apparently been no trouble at all, making his list of excuses that much more confusing.  Having worked in restaurant before, I just wanted to leave and never come back. There was so much wrong with this place, so much they could do to make it better.  Other issues: there’s no music or ambiance; there’s no chilly oil or other condiments on the table to season the incredibly bland food; this place is definitely violating health codes, at a nearby table unsealed food was marinating in a metal tray.

I have been to Uncle Sun twice. The service is extremely fast and the prices are great. The second time I went here I asked the waitress what she recommended. 👍She was very honest and helpful and recommended the orange chicken. I ordered that and pork buns--I've had the general tsos before so I knew what to expect. The quality of the meat is extremely poor. Never in my life have I encountered meat like it. It is dry and just a bizarre texture but each time I just go with it. The sauces are so sticky! You can almost pick it off the meat. The pork buns were gross. I've eaten pork buns on campus and they were amazing (shredded pork inside). The pork here was a weird, bland grey-brown lump. The outside of the buns were fine but inside it was a soggy mess. I took leftovers home of the chicken and ate it a few hours later. The chicken tasted sandy (?? So bizarre), it was like the meat changed entirely between me packaging it up at the restaurant and reheating it for two minutes in the microwave in my dorm. The texture stopped me from eating the rest. I was very disappointed.👎 If I could give one recommendation to the owners: you have an outstanding team in the kitchen--they work so fast--but I would appreciate fresh chicken or in the very least something different than what you have now. I like the idea of supporting a small local Chinese restaurant (hence my two visits) but even the dish the staff recommended did not satisfy me.

ABSOLUTELY RIDICULOUS. This restaurant advertises being open at 11am. We are from out of town, ordered lunch online at 12:00pm. After TWO HOURS waiting in our hotel room, the charge being PROCESSED on my credit card and SEVERAL unanswered calls to the resultant we finally drove to the location to see what on earth could be taking so long. It was DARK AND LOCKED. Door hours say 11:00am-10:00pm! Some homeless guy sitting outside said, and I quote, "They are never here. They come when they want. They won't even arrive till after 5 I bet."  We wasted THREE hours of our limited time here because of this ordeal. I now have to wait for my refund of money. When I called later all they could say was "Yeah.... Yeah.... we canceled it. We canceled." NO APOLOGY. NO EXPLINATION.  Rude staff. Absolutely unacceptable ordeal.  I'd never recommend this place. Besides, the nice homeless man said there's a better place right up the street anyways. Thanks man.
